## 2026-03-29 - BatchEditor cannot set selected tokens to an alias reference
- Added an "Alias" value-mode row to BatchEditor. A text input accepts a bare path (e.g. `color.brand.primary`) or `{path}` format and derives the canonical `{path}` reference. On focus/type it opens an `AliasAutocomplete` dropdown (reusing the existing component) positioned absolutely below the input. On select the field fills with `{path}` and the dropdown closes. `aliasActive` feeds into `hasOp` so the Apply button enables. In `handleApply`, when `aliasActive`, the patch sets `$value = aliasRef` for every selected token regardless of type. A preview line shows "Will set {ref} on N tokens" when a valid alias is chosen and the autocomplete is closed. State is cleared on successful apply.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/BatchEditor.tsx` ~L1, ~L81, ~L230, ~L316, ~L412, ~L733
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

